rComments: Amy is a queen! I am a social science student who was initially intimidated by the course content, but she made it so accessible and fun. I did study pretty thoroughly for the midterm because I was genuinely interested in the content and I got a 95. The class average was a 78. This was my favorite class this semester!

I really enjoyed this course, not only because I liked the nature of study, but the professor herself was incredibly sweet, understanding, knowledgable and accessible. As long as you attend lectures and prepare using her resources, you will pass/succeed

She is great! She makes material interesting although lectures can get boring. Her tests and grading are very fair.
